&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Part-time Practice Nurse required&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are delighted to offer a rare opportunity for a part time practice nurse to join our team.  We are looking for a highly motivated and enthusiastic team player who can demonstrate a high standard of clinical excellence and knowledge.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be expected to work closely as a team of two practice nurses and two health care assistants alongside a proactive, friendly, multidisciplinary team.&lt;span&gt;The post is based on a 3.5 day week (28.5 hours) and will include extended hours provision as part of the contract.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will have a background of chronic disease management, and will be expected to carry out the full range of practice nursing duties such as cervical cytology, childhood immunisations, travel vaccinations, family planning and health promotion.  Training could be provided for strong candidates to bring their skills in line with primary care requirements.   &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;





